definition: early autumn/7th month of the lunar calendar

sentences.english: The finished report is expected to be published in early autumn.
sentences.chinese: 最終的報告有望於今年初秋發佈。

sentences.english: Qinqin cool, Xiaoxiao rain, I walked into the original landscape in the early autumn.
sentences.chinese: 沁沁涼意，瀟瀟細雨，原來我已走進初秋的風景裏了。

sentences.english: The outbreaks occur most often in the summer and early fall.
sentences.chinese: 暴發最常發生在夏季和初秋。

sentences.english: Early autumn, day gradually cool, rainy season should read.
sentences.chinese: 初秋，天漸涼，微雨時節宜讀書。

sentences.english: I well remember how in the early autumn dawn I would run there as soon as I was awake.
sentences.chinese: 我清晰的記得初秋的黎明，我一醒來就往那裏跑。

sentences.english: Yesterday evening, I almost felt the early Autumn approaching in Jiangnan.
sentences.chinese: 昨天黃昏，已經感受到江南初秋的況味。

sentences.english: Indus leaves fall early, subtle early autumn will easily be blown.
sentences.chinese: 梧桐葉落早，淡淡的初秋便輕易將其吹落。

sentences.english: Collected here are a handful of recent images of early autumn around the northern half of our world.
sentences.chinese: 以下呈現給各位的是北半球初秋降臨人間的景象。

sentences.english: It is bright and fresh in early autumn.
sentences.chinese: 初秋的天氣格外明朗清新。

sentences.english: This is a fantasic favorite among natives of Nanjing in spring, summer and early autumn.
sentences.chinese: 南京人在春夏及初秋期間極喜食用。

sentences.english: All through the late summer and early fall, destructively heavy rains have wreaked havoc on southeast Asia.
sentences.chinese: 東南亞的暴雨從深夏貫穿到初秋，已經肆虐成災。
